[4] Mexico (Guanajuato)
Date: Fri 16 Oct 2009
Source: El Universal [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/notas/633836.html>


A [health] brigade of 120 people was charged with reducing the
presence of mosquitoes by 98 percent in the urban zone of the central
area of Silao.

The state Secretariat of Health this [Thu 15 Oct 2009] detected the
1st outbreak of classical dengue in the central area of Silao
municipality, announced the secretary of health, Armando Aguirre
Torres. The locally acquired cases include 6 women and a man [whose
samples] were submitted to the Guanajuato Regional Laboratory and
[the patients] were under medical treatment, said the official. These
patients are added to the 18 Guanajuato residents who were attacked
this year [2008] by _Aedes aegypti_ [transmitting dengue virus],
indicated the health official.

The mosquito vector of the disease [virus] is present in 28
municipalities of the state, with greatest incidence in the
industrial zone, among these Silao, Leon, Irapuato, Celaya, and
Salamanca. The official signaled that a health alert has been issued
in 46 municipalities of the state, with emphasis on localities where
the mosquito proliferates.

Aguirre Torres pointed out that actions have been intensified in
Silao with the formation of citizen networks for prevention and
health promotion based on the strategy of "clean patios" and
attention to [mosquito breeding in] stored water, with fogging using
heavy machines in public streets, portable equipment for use in
houses, backpack [equipment], and [mosquito] larva control through
house-to-house visits.

The official stressed that the ongoing epidemiological alert is due
to the proliferation of the vector, hence the importance of
maintaining the fight against _Aedes_ and cleanup measures,
elimination of trash and monitoring of stored water.

[Byline: Xochitl Alvarez]

