[7] Panama (Chiriqui)
Date: Tue 20 Oct 2009
Source: Critica en Linea [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.critica.com.pa/archivo/10202009/prov04.html>


The 639 classical dengue cases registered up to this past Tuesday [20
Oct 2009] in Chiriqui province practically constitute an epidemic, as
indicated by Pablo Acosta, regional chief of epidemiology of the
Ministry of Health.

He warned that people should take this problem seriously in order to
prevent larger ones. The circulation of several types of dengue virus
in the region increases the likelihood of reported new cases of DHF.

[Byline: Jose Vasquez]

